    "narrative": "Today\u2019s slate is headlined by **Corbin Carroll**, who commands the highest score of the day at 80.85. His matchup against Pop is ideal; beyond his elite speed\u2014a critical factor for our scarcity-driven strategy\u2014the combination of a favorable park shift and a high-order spot makes him our primary offensive engine. **Josh Naylor** also stands out as a strong play (69.07) against Bolton. While Bolton\u2019s xERA is mid-tier, the matchup dynamics and **Josh Naylor**\u2019s consistent position in the heart of the order provide a high floor that makes him a lock in our 1B slot. We are also monitoring **Mickey Moniak** closely; while his score of 65.00 is excellent, the 39% rain risk creates a volatile situation that could truncate his production if the game is delayed or called early.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench involved **Zach McKinstry**, who narrowly missed the cut with a 49.24 score. While his profile benefits from the slow delivery of Alcantara (97% SB probability), his spot at the bottom of the order (-6%) and the optimizer\u2019s preference for the higher efficiency ratings of **Seiya Suzuki** and **Tyler Soderstrom** kept him on the pine. Elsewhere, **Trevor Story** (67.13) provides sneaky upside against Pallante. The combination of wind blowing out and a slow opposing delivery gives him a significant boost in stolen base potential, making him a high-reward play despite a modest base projection. We are proceeding with this lineup while keeping a close eye on the weather; if the rain risk for **Mickey Moniak** increases, we will look to rotate in **Max Muncy** or **Zach McKinstry** to preserve our plate appearance caps without sacrificing too much offensive ceiling.",
